events.name: LSU Tigers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron threw three touchdown passes, T.J. Yeldon ran for 133 yards and two scores and No. 1 Alabama overwhelmed No. 10 LSU 38-17 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCarron guides No. 1 Bama by LSU

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Jameis Winston threw two touchdown passes, and No. 3 Florida State tied a school record with six interceptions in a 59-3 rout of Wake Forest on Saturday that clinched an ACC championship game berth.
headlines.shortLinkText: Winston, Florida St. overwhelm Wake

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Maty Mauk threw five touchdown passes, four to Dorial Green-Beckham, and No. 9 Missouri cruised past Kentucky 48-17 on Saturday.

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Nick Marshall gained 214 of Auburn's 444 yards rushing Saturday and the seventh-ranked Tigers scored on a punt return and kickoff return in a 55-23 victory over Tennessee.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Trey Edmunds ran for four touchdowns, the first three of them set up by Miami special-teams miscues, and Virginia Tech knocked off the 11th-ranked Hurricanes 42-24 on Saturday night.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw for 446 yards and tied a career-high with five touchdown passes to lead No. 15 Texas A&M to a 51-41 win Saturday over Mississippi State in what could be the Heisman Trophy winner's last home game.

venue.fullName: Jonah Field at War Memorial Stadium

headlines.description: Derek Carr threw for 366 yards and four touchdowns, and Josh Quezada rushed for 105 yards and a score as No. 16 Fresno State defeated Wyoming 48-10 Saturday night.

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Arizona Wildcats
